{"type":"message","id":"7ccc1eb1","parentId":"35e18f9c","timestamp":"2026-04-18T09:39:19.835Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lead confirmed. I need to:\n1. Create new branches for both BE and FE\n2. Spawn agents to implement the plan\n\nLet me start by creating the feature branches from the current develop, then spawn agents for both BE and FE work.\n\nWait, I need to check - the BE is on `fix/ci-git-pull-ff-only` and FE is on `feat/notification-channel`. After the merge, we need new branches from the merged state. But actually, the merges already happened on those branches. So I should create new feature branches from the current state.\n\nLet me create:\n- BE: `feat/exam-results-import` from current state\n- FE: `feat/exam-results-enhancement` from current state\n\n\nActually, looking back at the workflow rules - after merging, I should create new branches for the actual implementation work. The BE merge is already committed on `fix/ci-git-pull-ff-only` and FE on `feat/notification-channel`, so I'll spin up agents to handle the new feature development from there.","thinkingSignature":"458d9a259297e9c0f537197372acf165b33e91bee757b4c837d249f838cd18c8"},{"type":"text","text":"Confirm nhận rồi. Đang tạo branch mới và spawn agents.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5qp1vn9mqgw8_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-qlhv-be && git checkout -b feat/exam-results-enhancement && git push origin feat/exam-results-enhancement 2>&1 | tail -5","timeout":30}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5qp1vn9mqgw8_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-fe && git checkout -b feat/exam-results-enhancement && git push origin feat/exam-results-enhancement 2>&1 | tail -5","timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":0,"output":392,"cacheRead":39762,