{"type":"message","id":"7828b1ba","parentId":"7ccc1eb1","timestamp":"2026-04-18T09:39:22.169Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_5qp1vn9mqgw8_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Switched to a new branch 'feat/exam-results-enhancement'\nremote: To create a merge request for feat/exam-results-enhancement, visit:        \nremote:   https://gitlab.com/ahv-dtlx/ahv-qlhv-be/-/merge_requests/new?merge_request%5Bsource_branch%5D=feat%2Fexam-results-enhancement        \nremote: \nTo https://gitlab.com/ahv-dtlx/ahv-qlhv-be.git\n * [new branch]      feat/exam-results-enhancement -> feat/exam-results-enhancement"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":2178,"aggregated":"Switched to a new branch 'feat/exam-results-enhancement'\nremote: To create a merge request for feat/exam-results-enhancement, visit:        \nremote:   https://gitlab.com/ahv-dtlx/ahv-qlhv-be/-/merge_requests/new?merge_request%5Bsource_branch%5D=feat%2Fexam-results-enhancement        \nremote: \nTo https://gitlab.com/ahv-dtlx/ahv-qlhv-be.git\n * [new branch]      feat/exam-results-enhancement -> feat/exam-results-enhancement","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776505162121}}
{"type":"message","id":"9ec0ab48","parentId":"7828b1ba","timestamp":"2026-04-18T09:39:22.226Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_5qp1vn9mqgw8_2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Switched to a new branch 'feat/exam-results-enhancement'\nremote: To create a merge request for feat/exam-results-enhancement, visit:        \nremote:   https://gitlab.com/ahv-dtlx/ahv-qlhv-fe/-/merge_requests/new?merge_request%5Bsource_branch%5D=feat%2Fexam-results-enhancement        \nremote: \nTo https://gitlab.com/ahv-dtlx/ahv-qlhv-fe.git\n * [new branch]      feat/exam-results-enhancement -> feat/exam-results-enhancement"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":2103,"aggregated":"Switched to a new branch 'feat/exam-results-enhancement'\nremote: To create a merge request for feat/exam-results-enhancement, visit:        \nremote:   https://gitlab.com/ahv-dtlx/ahv-qlhv-fe/-/merge_requests/new?merge_request%5Bsource_branch%5D=feat%2Fexam-results-enhancement        \nremote: \nTo https://gitlab.com/ahv-dtlx/ahv-qlhv-fe.git\n * [new branch]      feat/exam-results-enhancement -> feat/exam-results-enhancement","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776505162170}}
{"type":"message","id":"91ce566c","parentId":"9ec0ab48","timestamp":"2026-04-18T09:40:05.485Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Both branches created and pushed. Now spawn agents for BE and FE.","thinkingSignature":"20e16e1d3583edb0fcc858dbb96952239ea7111f5e8596ab56157d47f884e2c8"},{"type":"text","text":"Branch đã push. Spawning 2 agents song song:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0z41s1ckjif9_1","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"task":"You are senior-backend working on ahv-qlhv-be.\n\n## MISSION\nImplement Phase 1 + Phase 2 of the exam results enhancement plan on branch `feat/exam-results-enhancement`.\n\n## WORKING DIR\n`/root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-qlhv-be`\n\n## CONTEXT\nCurrent branch: `feat/exam-results-enhancement` (already pushed, based on origin/develop with latest merged)\n\n### Goal: Enhance exam batch results tracking\n\n## PHASE 1 — Expand Data Model\n\n### 1.1 Edit `src/infrastructure/database/models/exam_batch.model.ts`\nChange `studentResults` item schema from:\n```ts\nstudentResults: [{ type: Schema.Types.Mixed }]\n```\nTo a proper sub-schema:\n```ts\nstudentResults: [{\n  student_id: { type: String, required: true },\n  name: { type: String, required: true },\n  result: { \n    type: String, \n    enum: ['pass', 'fail', 'absent', 'no_result'], \n    default: 'no_result' \n  },\n  theory_result: { type: String, enum: ['pass', 'fail', 'absent'] },\n  simulation_result: { type: String, enum: ['pass', 'fail', 'absent'] },\n  parking_result: { type: String, enum: ['pass', 'fail', 'absent'] },     // sa hình\n  road_result: { type: String, enum: ['pass', 'fail', 'absent'] },        // đường trường\n  note: { type: String, default: '' },\n}]\n```\n\n### 1.2 Edit `src/application/services/exam_batch.service.ts`\n\nAdd a `getBatchStats(batchId: string)` method that returns:\n```ts\n{\n  total: number,\n  passed: number,\n  failed: number,\n  absent: number,\n  noResult: number,\n  failedBySection: {\n    theory: number,\n    simulation: number,\n    parking: number,\n    road: number\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThe logic:\n- `total` = studentResults.length\n- `passed` = filter where result === 'pass'\n- `failed` = filter where result === 'fail'\n- `absent` = filter where result === 'absent'\n- `noResult` = filter where result === 'no_result'\n- `failedBySection.theory` = filter where theory_result === 'fail'\n- `failedBySection.simulation` = filter where simulation_result === 'fail'\n- `failedBySection.parking` = filter where parking_result === 'fail'\n- `failedBySection.road` = filter where road_result === 'fail'\n\nAlso update the `exportBatchesToExcel` columns to include:\n- Add column: \"Vắng thi\" with key `absent`\n- Add columns: \"Trượt lý thuyết\", \"Trượt mô phỏng\", \"Trượt sa hình\", \"Trượt đường trường\"\n\n### 1.3 Add Import Excel endpoint\n\nCreate new file: `src/interface/controllers/exam_import.controller.ts`\n```ts\nimport { Request, Response } from 'express';\nimport { ExamBatchService } from '@/application/services/exam_batch.service';\nimport { catchAsync } from '@/interface/middlewares/catchAsync.middleware';\n\nconst examBatchService = new ExamBatchService();\n\nexport const importExamResults = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  // Expect file via multer: req.file\n  // Parse Excel using ExcelHelper or xlsx library\n  // Expected columns in Excel: student_id, name, result, theory_result, simulation_result, parking_result, road_result, note\n  // Update each student in the batch's studentResults array\n  // If student not found in batch, skip or add\n  const { batchId } = req.body;\n  const file = (req as any).file;\n  \n  if (!file) {\n    return res.statusError('No file uploaded', 400);\n  }\n  if (!batchId) {\n    return res.statusError('batchId is required', 400);\n  }\n  \n  // Parse Excel: use xlsx library (already installed)\n  const XLSX = require('xlsx');\n  const workbook = XLSX.read(file.buffer, { type: 'buffer' });\n  const sheet = workbook.Sheets[workbook.SheetNames[0]];\n  const rows: any[] = XLSX.utils.sheet_to_json(sheet);\n  \n  // Validate required columns\n  const requiredCols = ['student_id', 'result'];\n  const missing = requiredCols.filter(c => !(c in (rows[0] || {})));\n  if (missing.length > 0) {\n    return res.statusError(`Missing required columns: ${missing.join(', ')}`, 400);\n  }\n  \n  // Get batch\n  const batch = await examBatchService.getBatchById(batchId);\n  if (!batch) {\n    return res.statusError('Exam batch not found', 404);\n  }\n  \n  // Map results: update or add\n  const existingMap = new Map(\n    (batch.studentResults || []).map((r: any) => [r.student_id, r])\n  );\n  \n  for (const row of rows) {\n    existingMap.set(row.student_id, {\n      student_id: String(row.student_id),\n      name: String(row.name || row.student_id),\n      result: ['pass', 'fail', 'absent', 'no_result'].includes(row.result) ? row.result : 'no_result',\n      theory_result: row.theory_result || undefined,\n      simulation_result: row.simulation_result || undefined,\n      parking_result: row.parking_result || undefined,\n      road_result: row.road_result || undefined,\n      note: String(row.note || ''),\n    });\n  }\n  \n  await examBatchService.updateBatch(batchId, { \n    studentResults: Array.from(existingMap.values()) \n  });\n  \n  res.statusSuccess({ imported: rows.length }, 'Import thành công');\n});\n```\n\nAlso add `getBatchStats` endpoint to controller.\n\n### 1.4 Add routes\n\nEdit `src/interface/routes/exam_batch.routes.ts`:\n```ts\nimport { importExamResults, getBatchStats } from '@/interface/controllers/exam_import.controller';\n\n// Add routes:\nrouter.post('/:id/import-results', upload.single('file'), importExamResults);\nrouter.get('/:id/stats', getBatchStats);\n```\n\nImport multer and xlsx if needed:\n```ts\nimport multer from 'multer';\nconst upload = multer({ storage: multer.memoryStorage() });\n```\n\nMake sure xlsx is installed:\n```bash\nyarn add xlsx && yarn add -D @types/xlsx\n```\n\n### 1.5 Run build\n```bash\nyarn build\n```\nFix any TypeScript errors. Must pass.\n\n### 1.6 Commit\n```bash\ngit add . && git commit -m \"feat(exam): enhance batch results with absent tracking, per-section results, and Excel import\"\n```\n\n## RULES\n- ALWAYS use prompt-optimizer before spawning sub-agents\n- Use yarn, never npm\n- Always yarn build before commit\n- NEVER push — only commit locally, wait for Lead to tell you to push\n- After all changes pass build, commit and report what was done\n","label":"ahv-qlhv-be:senior-backend","runtime":"subagent","agentId":"senior-backend","mode":"session"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0z41s1ckjif9_2","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"task":"You are senior-frontend working on ahv-qlhv-fe.\n\n## MISSION\nImplement Phase 2 + Phase 3 of the exam results enhancement plan on branch `feat/exam-results-enhancement`.\n\n## WORKING DIR\n`/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-fe`\n\n## CONTEXT\nCurrent branch: `feat/exam-results-enhancement` (already pushed, based on origin/develop with latest merged)\n\n### Goal: Enhance exam batch results tracking UI\n\n## PHASE 2 — Import Excel Modal (FE)\n\n### 2.1 Create Import Modal\nCreate file: `src/components/sat-hach/ImportResultsModal.tsx`\n\nThe modal should:\n- Accept a `batchId` and `batchName` prop\n- Show a drag-and-drop or click-to-upload zone for Excel files\n- Use fetch with FormData to POST to `/api/v1/exam-batches/${batchId}/import-results`\n- Support file types: .xlsx, .xls, .csv\n- Show success/error toast via `sonner`\n- Call `onSuccess` callback on success\n\nExcel template columns (documented in UI):\n```\nstudent_id | name | result | theory_result | simulation_result | parking_result | road_result | note\n```\n- `result`: pass | fail | absent | no_result\n- `theory_result`: pass | fail | absent (optional)\n- `simulation_result`: pass | fail | absent (optional)\n- `parking_result`: pass | fail | absent (optional) — \"sa hình\"\n- `road_result`: pass | fail | absent (optional) — \"đường trường\"\n\n### 2.2 Update examService.ts\nAdd:\n```ts\nexport const importExamResults = async (batchId: string, file: File) => {\n  const formData = new FormData();\n  formData.append('file', file);\n  formData.append('batchId', batchId);\n  const response = await fetch(`${API_BASE_URL}/exam-batches/${batchId}/import-results`, {\n    method: 'POST',\n    headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${getToken()}` },\n    body: formData,\n  });\n  return response.json();\n};\n```\n\nAlso add:\n```ts\nexport const getBatchStats = async (batchId: string) => {\n  const response = await fetch(`${API_BASE_URL}/exam-batches/${batchId}/stats`, {\n    headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${getToken()}` },\n  });\n  return response.json();\n};\n```\n\n## PHASE 3 — Update sat-hach/page.tsx\n\n### 3.1 Add \"Import kết quả\" button\nIn the expanded panel of each exam batch, add an \"Import kết quả\" button next to \"Xuất Excel\" header button.\n- Opens the ImportResultsModal\n- Passes batch._id and batch.name\n\n### 3.2 Update stats display in expanded panel\nFor each batch, compute:\n- `absentCount` = exam.studentResults?.filter((r: any) => r.result === 'absent').length\n- Add a \"Absent\" stat chip in the right-side stats box\n\nExample UI addition to the stats box:\n```tsx\n<div className=\"flex flex-col border-l border-gray-100 pl-4\">\n  <span className=\"text-lg font-black text-gray-400 leading-none\">{absentCount}</span>\n  <span className=\"text-[9px] font-bold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-widest mt-1\">Vắng</span>\n</div>\n```\n\n### 3.3 Update ResultModal for per-section results\nModify `src/components/sat-hach/ResultModal.tsx` to add sub-section result inputs:\n\nAdd state:\n```ts\nconst [theoryResult, setTheoryResult] = useState('');\nconst [simulationResult, setSimulationResult] = useState('');\nconst [parkingResult, setParkingResult] = useState('');\nconst [roadResult, setRoadResult] = useState('');\n```\n\nAdd these as additional select fields in the modal body (after the main result select), each with options: \"Chưa có\" | \"Đạt\" | \"Trượt\" | \"Vắng\"\n\nThe `onSave` callback should pass all results:\n```ts\nawait onSave({\n  result,\n  theory_result: theoryResult === 'no_result' ? undefined : theoryResult,\n  simulation_result: simulationResult === 'no_result' ? undefined : simulationResult,\n  parking_result: parkingResult === 'no_result' ? undefined : parkingResult,\n  road_result: roadResult === 'no_result' ? undefined : roadResult,\n  note\n});\n```\n\nActually, update the `ResultModal` interface to accept the sub-results from the student object too, pre-populating them if available.\n\n### 3.4 Update handleSaveResult in sat-hach/page.tsx\nThe `handleSaveResult` function should send the new shape:\n```ts\nconst updatedResults = (batch.studentResults || []).map((s: any) => {\n  if (s.student_id === targetStudentForResults.id) {\n    return { \n      ...s, \n      result, \n      theory_result: theoryResult,\n      simulation_result: simulationResult,\n      parking_result: parkingResult,\n      road_result: roadResult,\n      note \n    };\n  }\n  return s;\n});\n```\n\n## RULES\n- ALWAYS use yarn, never npm\n- Always yarn build before commit\n- NEVER push — only commit locally, wait for Lead to tell you to push\n- After all changes pass build, commit and report what was done\n- The working dir is: `/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-fe`\n","label":"ahv-qlhv-fe:senior-frontend","runtime":"subagent","agentId":"senior-frontend","mode":"session"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":319,"output":2960,"cacheRead":41253,"cacheWrite":1414,"totalTokens":45946,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776505162229,"responseId":"0632844bd69a51c01a2ff