{"type":"message","id":"e6f25c87","parentId":"4025b8d4","timestamp":"2026-04-18T09:40:48.421Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Need to add thread=true for session mode.","thinkingSignature":"d0501ca1760c83ec0ea4b6d63ed99fc6b68967358574292eb4f3578cf7e0acac"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xlmxbxt70r6v_1","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"task":"You are senior-backend working on ahv-qlhv-be.\n\n## MISSION\nImplement Phase 1 + Phase 2 of the exam results enhancement plan on branch `feat/exam-results-enhancement`.\n\n## WORKING DIR\n`/root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-qlhv-be`\n\n## CONTEXT\nCurrent branch: `feat/exam-results-enhancement` (already pushed, based on origin/develop with latest merged)\n\n### Goal: Enhance exam batch results tracking\n\n## PHASE 1 — Expand Data Model\n\n### 1.1 Edit `src/infrastructure/database/models/exam_batch.model.ts`\nChange `studentResults` item schema from:\n```ts\nstudentResults: [{ type: Schema.Types.Mixed }]\n```\nTo a proper sub-schema:\n```ts\nstudentResults: [{\n  student_id: { type: String, required: true },\n  name: { type: String, required: true },\n  result: { \n    type: String, \n    enum: ['pass', 'fail', 'absent', 'no_result'], \n    default: 'no_result' \n  },\n  theory_result: { type: String, enum: ['pass', 'fail', 'absent'] },\n  simulation_result: { type: String, enum: ['pass', 'fail', 'absent'] },\n  parking_result: { type: String, enum: ['pass', 'fail', 'absent'] },     // sa hình\n  road_result: { type: String, enum: ['pass', 'fail', 'absent'] },        // đường trường\n  note: { type: String, default: '' },\n}]\n```\n\n### 1.2 Edit `src/application/services/exam_batch.service.ts`\n\nAdd a `getBatchStats(batchId: string)` method that returns:\n```ts\n{\n  total: number,\n  passed: number,\n  failed: number,\n  absent: number,\n  noResult: number,\n  failedBySection: {\n    theory: number,\n    simulation: number,\n    parking: number,\n    road: number\n  }\n}\n```\n\nLogic:\n- total = studentResults.length\n- passed = filter result === 'pass'\n- failed = filter result === 'fail'\n- absent = filter result === 'absent'\n- noResult = filter result === 'no_result'\n- failedBySection.theory = filter theory_result === 'fail'\n- failedBySection.simulation = filter simulation_result === 'fail'\n- failedBySection.parking = filter parking_result === 'fail'\n- failedBySection.road = filter road_result === 'fail'\n\nAlso update exportBatchesToExcel to add columns:\n- \"Vắng thi\" with key `absent`\n- \"Trượt lý thuyết\" with key `failedTheory`\n- \"Trượt mô phỏng\" with key `failedSimulation`\n- \"Trượt sa hình\" with key `failedParking`\n- \"Trượt đường trường\" with key `failedRoad`\n\n### 1.3 Create `src/interface/controllers/exam_import.controller.ts`\n```ts\nimport { Request, Response } from 'express';\nimport { ExamBatchService } from '@/application/services/exam_batch.service';\nimport { catchAsync } from '@/interface/middlewares/catchAsync.middleware';\nimport multer from 'multer';\n\nconst examBatchService = new ExamBatchService();\nconst upload = multer({ storage: multer.memoryStorage() });\n\nexport const importExamResults = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const file = (req as any).file;\n  const { batchId } = req.body;\n  \n  if (!file) return res.statusError('No file uploaded', 400);\n  if (!batchId) return res.statusError('batchId is required', 400);\n  \n  const XLSX = require('xlsx');\n  const workbook = XLSX.read(file.buffer, { type: 'buffer' });\n  const sheet = workbook.Sheets[workbook.SheetNames[0]];\n  const rows: any[] = XLSX.utils.sheet_to_json(sheet);\n  \n  const batch = await examBatchService.getBatchById(batchId);\n  if (!batch) return res.statusError('Exam batch not found', 404);\n  \n  const existingMap = new Map(\n    (batch.studentResults || []).map((r: any) => [r.student_id, r])\n  );\n  \n  for (const row of rows) {\n    existingMap.set(String(row.student_id), {\n      student_id: String(row.student_id),\n      name: String(row.name || row.student_id),\n      result: ['pass', 'fail', 'absent', 'no_result'].includes(row.result) ? row.result : 'no_result',\n      theory_result: row.theory_result || undefined,\n      simulation_result: row.simulation_result || undefined,\n      parking_result: row.parking_result || undefined,\n      road_result: row.road_result || undefined,\n      note: String(row.note || ''),\n    });\n  }\n  \n  await examBatchService.updateBatch(batchId, { \n    studentResults: Array.from(existingMap.values()) \n  });\n  \n  res.statusSuccess({ imported: rows.length }, 'Import thành công');\n});\n\nexport const getBatchStats = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const idStr = typeof req.params.id === 'string' ? req.params.id : req.params.id[0];\n  const stats = await examBatchService.getBatchStats(idStr);\n  res.statusSuccess(stats, 'Batch stats retrieved');\n});\n```\n\n### 1.4 Edit `src/interface/routes/exam_batch.routes.ts`\nAdd:\n```ts\nimport { importExamResults, getBatchStats } from '@/interface/controllers/exam_import.controller';\n\nrouter.post('/:id/import-results', upload.single('file'), importExamResults);\nrouter.get('/:id/stats', getBatchStats);\n```\n\n### 1.5 Install xlsx\n```bash\ncd /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-qlhv-be && yarn add xlsx && yarn add -D @types/xlsx\n```\n\n### 1.6 Build\n```bash\nyarn build\n```\nFix any TypeScript errors. Must pass.\n\n### 1.7 Commit\n```bash\ngit add . && git commit -m \"feat(exam): enhance batch results with absent tracking, per-section results, and Excel import\"\n```\n\n## RULES\n- Use yarn, never npm\n- Always yarn build before commit\n- NEVER push — only commit locally\n- After build passes, commit and report what was done\n","label":"ahv-qlhv-be:senior-backend","runtime":"subagent","agentId":"senior-backend","thread":true,"mode":"session"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xlmxbxt70r6v_2","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"task":"You are senior-frontend working on ahv-qlhv-fe.\n\n## MISSION\nImplement Phase 2 + Phase 3 of the exam results enhancement plan on branch `feat/exam-results-enhancement`.\n\n## WORKING DIR\n`/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-fe`\n\n## CONTEXT\nCurrent branch: `feat/exam-results-enhancement` (already pushed)\n\n## PHASE 2 — Import Excel Modal (FE)\n\n### 2.1 Create `src/components/sat-hach/ImportResultsModal.tsx`\nA modal component that:\n- Props: `{ isOpen, onClose, batchId, batchName, onSuccess }`\n- Has a file upload zone (drag-drop or click)\n- Accepts: .xlsx, .xls, .csv\n- Uploads to: POST `/api/v1/exam-batches/${batchId}/import-results` with FormData\n- Uses the auth token from `localStorage` or a helper\n- Shows loading spinner while uploading\n- Shows success toast on success, error toast on failure\n- Calls `onSuccess()` after successful import\n- Beautiful UI matching the existing design language (rounded corners, indigo theme)\n\n### 2.2 Update `src/services/examService.ts`\nAdd two new functions:\n```ts\nexport const importExamResults = async (batchId: string, file: File) => {\n  const formData = new FormData();\n  formData.append('file', file);\n  formData.append('batchId', batchId);\n  const token = typeof window !== 'undefined' ? localStorage.getItem('accessToken') : '';\n  const response = await fetch(`${process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL}/api/v1/exam-batches/${batchId}/import-results`, {\n    method: 'POST',\n    headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${token}` },\n    body: formData,\n  });\n  return response.json();\n};\n\nexport const getBatchStats = async (batchId: string) => {\n  const token = typeof window !== 'undefined' ? localStorage.getItem('accessToken') : '';\n  const response = await fetch(`${process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL}/api/v1/exam-batches/${batchId}/stats`, {\n    headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${token}` },\n  });\n  return response.json();\n};\n```\n\n## PHASE 3 — Update `src/app/sat-hach/page.tsx`\n\n### 3.1 Import the new modal\n```ts\nimport ImportResultsModal from '@/src/components/sat-hach/ImportResultsModal';\n```\n\n### 3.2 Add state for import modal\n```ts\nconst [importModalOpen, setImportModalOpen] = useState(false);\nconst [targetBatchForImport, setTargetBatchForImport] = useState<{ id: string, name: string } | null>(null);\n```\n\n### 3.3 Add \"Import kết quả\" button\nIn the header area (next to \"Xuất Excel\" button), add:\n```tsx\n<button\n  onClick={() => {\n    setTargetBatchForImport({ id: exam._id, name: exam.name });\n    setImportModalOpen(true);\n  }}\n  className=\"flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 bg-white border border-gray-200 text-gray-700 font-bold rounded-xl hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors shadow-sm text-sm\"\n>\n  <Upload className=\"w-4 h-4\" /> Import kết quả\n</button>\n```\nNote: import `Upload` from `lucide-react`.\n\nAdd the Upload import:\n```ts\nimport { ..., Upload } from 'lucide-react';\n```\n\n### 3.4 Add absent count in expanded panel stats box\nCompute absent count for each batch:\n```ts\nconst absentCount = exam.studentResults?.filter((r: any) => r.result === 'absent').length || 0;\n```\n\nAdd to the stats display box:\n```tsx\n<div className=\"flex flex-col border-l border-gray-100 pl-4\">\n  <span className=\"text-lg font-black text-gray-400 leading-none\">{absentCount}</span>\n  <span className=\"text-[9px] font-bold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-widest mt-1\">Vắng</span>\n</div>\n```\n\n### 3.5 Update ResultModal for per-section results\n\nModify `src/components/sat-hach/ResultModal.tsx`:\n\nAdd new state variables after the existing state declarations:\n```ts\nconst [theoryResult, setTheoryResult] = useState('no_result');\nconst [simulationResult, setSimulationResult] = useState('no_result');\nconst [parkingResult, setParkingResult] = useState('no_result');\nconst [roadResult, setRoadResult] = useState('no_result');\n```\n\nPre-populate from student data (in useEffect):\n```ts\nif (isOpen && student) {\n  setResult(student.currentResult || 'no_result');\n  setNote(student.currentNote || '');\n  setTheoryResult(student.theoryResult || 'no_result');\n  setSimulationResult(student.simulationResult || 'no_result');\n  setParkingResult(student.parkingResult || 'no_result');\n  setRoadResult(student.roadResult || 'no_result');\n  setTouched({});\n  setErrors({});\n}\n```\n\nUpdate the interface to include sub-results:\n```ts\nstudent: { id: string; name: string; licenseClass: string; currentResult?: string; currentNote?: string; theoryResult?: string; simulationResult?: string; parkingResult?: string; roadResult?: string } | null;\n```\n\nAdd sub-section select fields in the modal body (after the main result select):\n```tsx\n<div className=\"grid grid-cols-2 gap-3\">\n  <FieldWrapper label=\"LÝ THUYẾT\" field=\"theory\">\n    <select value={theoryResult} onChange={e => setTheoryResult(e.target.value)}\n      className=\"w-full px-4 py-3 bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-xl text-sm font-medium focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-indigo-500/10 cursor-pointer appearance-none\">\n      <option value=\"no_result\">Chưa có</option>\n      <option value=\"pass\">Đạt</option>\n      <option value=\"fail\">Trượt</option>\n      <option value=\"absent\">Vắng</option>\n    </select>\n  </FieldWrapper>\n  <FieldWrapper label=\"MÔ PHỎNG\" field=\"simulation\">\n    <select value={simulationResult} onChange={e => setSimulationResult(e.target.value)}\n      className=\"w-full px-4 py-3 bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-xl text-sm font-medium focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-indigo-500/10 cursor-pointer appearance-none\">\n      <option value=\"no_result\">Chưa có</option>\n      <option value=\"pass\">Đạt</option>\n      <option value=\"fail\">Trượt</option>\n      <option value=\"absent\">Vắng</option>\n    </select>\n  </FieldWrapper>\n  <FieldWrapper label=\"SA HÌNH\" field=\"parking\">\n    <select value={parkingResult} onChange={e => setParkingResult(e.target.value)}\n      className=\"w-full px-4 py-3 bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-xl text-sm font-medium focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-indigo-500/10 cursor-pointer appearance-none\">\n      <option value=\"no_result\">Chưa có</option>\n      <option value=\"pass\">Đạt</option>\n      <option value=\"fail\">Trượt</option>\n      <option value=\"absent\">Vắng</option>\n    </select>\n  </FieldWrapper>\n  <FieldWrapper label=\"ĐƯỜNG TRƯỜNG\" field=\"road\">\n    <select value={roadResult} onChange={e => setRoadResult(e.target.value)}\n      className=\"w-full px-4 py-3 bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-xl text-sm font-medium focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-indigo-500/10 cursor-pointer appearance-none\">\n      <option value=\"no_result\">Chưa có</option>\n      <option value=\"pass\">Đạt</option>\n      <option value=\"fail\">Trượt</option>\n      <option value=\"absent\">Vắng</option>\n    </select>\n  </FieldWrapper>\n</div>\n```\n\nUpdate the handleSave function in the parent (sat-hach/page.tsx) to handle sub-results:\n```ts\nconst handleSaveResult = async (saveData: any) => {\n  // saveData = { result, theory_result, simulation_result, parking_result, road_result, note }\n  const { result, theory_result, simulation_result, parking_result, road_result, note } = saveData;\n  // ... existing batch fetch logic ...\n  const updatedResults = (batch.studentResults || []).map((s: any) => {\n    if (s.student_id === targetStudentForResults.id) {\n      return { ...s, result, theory_result, simulation_result, parking_result, road_result, note };\n    }\n    return s;\n  });\n  await updateExamBatch(batch._id || batch.id, { studentResults: updatedResults });\n};\n```\n\nNote: You'll need to update the ResultModal's onSave prop signature. Instead of `(result: string, note: string)`, change it to `(data: object)`. Update the modal's handleSave to pass an object instead.\n\nIn ResultModal, change handleSave:\n```ts\nconst handleSave = async () => {\n  // ... validation ...\n  await onSave({ \n    result, \n    theory_result: theoryResult === 'no_result' ? undefined : theoryResult,\n    simulation_result: simulationResult === 'no_result' ? undefined : simulationResult,\n    parking_result: parkingResult === 'no_result' ? undefined : parkingResult,\n    road_result: roadResult === 'no_result' ? undefined : roadResult,\n    note \n  });\n  onClose();\n};\n```\n\nAlso update the ResultModal's `onSave` prop type:\n```ts\nonSave: (data: { result: string; theory_result?: string; simulation_result?: string; parking_result?: string; road_result?: string; note: string }) => Promise<void>;\n```\n\n### 3.6 Add ImportResultsModal to page JSX\n```tsx\n<ImportResultsModal\n  isOpen={importModalOpen}\n  onClose={() => { setImportModalOpen(false); setTargetBatchForImport(null); }}\n  batchId={targetBatchForImport?.id || ''}\n  batchName={targetBatchForImport?.name || ''}\n  onSuccess={() => {\n    setImportModalOpen(false);\n    setTargetBatchForImport(null);\n    fetchExams();\n  }}\n/>\n```\n\n## BUILD & COMMIT\n\nAfter all changes:\n```bash\nyarn build\n```\nFix any TypeScript errors. Commit:\n```bash\ngit add . && git commit -m \"feat(exam): enhance UI with absent count, per-section results modal, and Excel import\"\n```\n\n## RULES\n- Use yarn, never npm\n- Always yarn build before commit\n- NEVER push — only commit locally\n- Working dir: `/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-fe`\n","label":"ahv-qlhv-fe:senior-frontend","runtime":"subagent","agentId":"senior-frontend","thread":true,"mode":"session"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":140,"output":4028,"cacheRead":42270,"cacheWrite":3614,"totalTokens":50052,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776505205793,"responseId":"0632847614e6b5482999dabe2c7b3542"}}
