{"type":"message","id":"ced839e8","parentId":"fd69b517","timestamp":"2026-04-18T09:41:49.087Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"thread=true is unavailable. Let me use mode=\"run\" instead for one-shot execution.","thinkingSignature":"fc406c5aec7985b741fce88ce5885d106e19090ea2aeb5bfc4098f4265be54f3"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gstz750cd44q_1","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"task":"You are senior-backend working on ahv-qlhv-be.\n\n## MISSION\nImplement Phase 1 + Phase 2 of the exam results enhancement plan on branch `feat/exam-results-enhancement`.\n\n## WORKING DIR\n`/root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-qlhv-be`\n\n## CONTEXT\nCurrent branch: `feat/exam-results-enhancement` (already pushed, based on origin/develop with latest merged)\n\n## PHASE 1 — Expand Data Model\n\n### 1.1 Edit `src/infrastructure/database/models/exam_batch.model.ts`\nChange `studentResults` item schema from:\n```ts\nstudentResults: [{ type: Schema.Types.Mixed }]\n```\nTo a proper sub-schema:\n```ts\nstudentResults: [{\n  student_id: { type: String, required: true },\n  name: { type: String, required: true },\n  result: { \n    type: String, \n    enum: ['pass', 'fail', 'absent', 'no_result'], \n    default: 'no_result' \n  },\n  theory_result: { type: String, enum: ['pass', 'fail', 'absent'] },\n  simulation_result: { type: String, enum: ['pass', 'fail', 'absent'] },\n  parking_result: { type: String, enum: ['pass', 'fail', 'absent'] },\n  road_result: { type: String, enum: ['pass', 'fail', 'absent'] },\n  note: { type: String, default: '' },\n}]\n```\n\n### 1.2 Edit `src/application/services/exam_batch.service.ts`\n\nAdd a `getBatchStats(batchId: string)` method:\n```ts\nasync getBatchStats(batchId: string) {\n  const batch = await this.examBatchRepository.findById(batchId);\n  if (!batch) throw new Error('Batch not found');\n  \n  const results: any[] = batch.studentResults || [];\n  const total = results.length;\n  const passed = results.filter(r => r.result === 'pass').length;\n  const failed = results.filter(r => r.result === 'fail').length;\n  const absent = results.filter(r => r.result === 'absent').length;\n  const noResult = results.filter(r => r.result === 'no_result').length;\n  \n  return {\n    total,\n    passed,\n    failed,\n    absent,\n    noResult,\n    failedBySection: {\n      theory: results.filter(r => r.theory_result === 'fail').length,\n      simulation: results.filter(r => r.simulation_result === 'fail').length,\n      parking: results.filter(r => r.parking_result === 'fail').length,\n      road: results.filter(r => r.road_result === 'fail').length,\n    }\n  };\n}\n```\n\nUpdate exportBatchesToExcel columns — add before the `total` column line:\n```ts\n{ header: 'Vắng thi', key: 'absent', width: 10 },\n{ header: 'Trượt lý thuyết', key: 'failedTheory', width: 14 },\n{ header: 'Trượt mô phỏng', key: 'failedSimulation', width: 14 },\n{ header: 'Trượt sa hình', key: 'failedParking', width: 13 },\n{ header: 'Trượt đường trường', key: 'failedRoad', width: 14 },\n```\n\nAnd in the data map (after `failed`):\n```ts\nabsent: absentCount,\nfailedTheory: results.filter((r: any) => r.theory_result === 'fail').length,\nfailedSimulation: results.filter((r: any) => r.simulation_result === 'fail').length,\nfailedParking: results.filter((r: any) => r.parking_result === 'fail').length,\nfailedRoad: results.filter((r: any) => r.road_result === 'fail').length,\n```\n\n### 1.3 Create `src/interface/controllers/exam_import.controller.ts`\n```ts\nimport { Request, Response } from 'express';\nimport { ExamBatchService } from '@/application/services/exam_batch.service';\nimport { ExamBatchRepository } from '@/infrastructure/database/repositories/exam_batch.repository';\nimport { catchAsync } from '@/interface/middlewares/catchAsync.middleware';\nimport multer from 'multer';\n\nconst examBatchRepository = new ExamBatchRepository();\nconst examBatchService = new ExamBatchService(examBatchRepository);\nconst upload = multer({ storage: multer.memoryStorage() });\n\nexport const importExamResults = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const file = (req as any).file;\n  const { batchId } = req.body;\n  \n  if (!file) return res.statusError('No file uploaded', 400);\n  if (!batchId) return res.statusError('batchId is required', 400);\n  \n  const XLSX = require('xlsx');\n  const workbook = XLSX.read(file.buffer, { type: 'buffer' });\n  const sheet = workbook.Sheets[workbook.SheetNames[0]];\n  const rows: any[] = XLSX.utils.sheet_to_json(sheet);\n  \n  if (rows.length === 0) return res.statusError('File is empty', 400);\n  \n  const batch = await examBatchService.getBatchById(batchId);\n  if (!batch) return res.statusError('Exam batch not found', 404);\n  \n  const existingMap = new Map(\n    (batch.studentResults || []).map((r: any) => [r.student_id, r])\n  );\n  \n  for (const row of rows) {\n    existingMap.set(String(row.student_id), {\n      student_id: String(row.student_id),\n      name: String(row.name || row.student_id),\n      result: ['pass', 'fail', 'absent', 'no_result'].includes(row.result) ? row.result : 'no_result',\n      theory_result: ['pass', 'fail', 'absent'].includes(row.theory_result) ? row.theory_result : undefined,\n      simulation_result: ['pass', 'fail', 'absent'].includes(row.simulation_result) ? row.simulation_result : undefined,\n      parking_result: ['pass', 'fail', 'absent'].includes(row.parking_result) ? row.parking_result : undefined,\n      road_result: ['pass', 'fail', 'absent'].includes(row.road_result) ? row.road_result : undefined,\n      note: String(row.note || ''),\n    });\n  }\n  \n  await examBatchService.updateBatch(batchId, { \n    studentResults: Array.from(existingMap.values()) \n  });\n  \n  res.statusSuccess({ imported: rows.length }, 'Import thành công');\n});\n\nexport const getBatchStats = catchAsync(async (req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const idStr = typeof req.params.id === 'string' ? req.params.id : req.params.id[0];\n  const stats = await examBatchService.getBatchStats(idStr);\n  res.statusSuccess(stats, 'Batch stats retrieved');\n});\n```\n\n### 1.4 Edit `src/interface/routes/exam_batch.routes.ts`\nRead the current file first, then add the new routes. Import at the top:\n```ts\nimport { importExamResults, getBatchStats } from '@/interface/controllers/exam_import.controller';\n```\n\nAdd routes at the end:\n```ts\nrouter.post('/:id/import-results', upload.single('file'), importExamResults);\nrouter.get('/:id/stats', getBatchStats);\n```\n\n### 1.5 Install xlsx\n```bash\ncd /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-qlhv-be && yarn add xlsx && yarn add -D @types/xlsx 2>&1 | tail -5\n```\n\n### 1.6 Build\n```bash\ncd /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-qlhv-be && yarn build 2>&1 | tail -15\n```\nFix any TypeScript errors until it passes.\n\n### 1.7 Commit\n```bash\ncd /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-qlhv-be && git add . && git commit -m \"feat(exam): enhance batch results with absent tracking, per-section results, and Excel import\"\n```\n\n## RULES\n- Use yarn, never npm\n- Always yarn build before commit\n- NEVER push — only commit locally\n- Report exactly what was done after commit\n","label":"ahv-qlhv-be:senior-backend","runtime":"subagent","agentId":"senior-backend","mode":"run"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gstz750cd44q_2","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"task":"You are senior-frontend working on ahv-qlhv-fe.\n\n## MISSION\nImplement Phase 2 + Phase 3 of the exam results enhancement plan on branch `feat/exam-results-enhancement`.\n\n## WORKING DIR\n`/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-fe`\n\n## CONTEXT\nCurrent branch: `feat/exam-results-enhancement` (already pushed)\n\n## PHASE 2 — Import Excel Modal (FE)\n\n### 2.1 Create `src/components/sat-hach/ImportResultsModal.tsx`\n\n```tsx\n\"use client\";\n\nimport React, { useState, useRef } from 'react';\nimport { X, Upload, Loader2, FileSpreadsheet, CheckCircle2, AlertCircle } from 'lucide-react';\nimport { toast } from 'sonner';\nimport { importExamResults } from '@/src/services/examService';\n\ninterface ImportResultsModalProps {\n  isOpen: boolean;\n  onClose: () => void;\n  batchId: string;\n  batchName: string;\n  onSuccess: () => void;\n}\n\nexport default function ImportResultsModal({ isOpen, onClose, batchId, batchName, onSuccess }: ImportResultsModalProps) {\n  const [file, setFile] = useState<File | null>(null);\n  const [isUploading, setIsUploading] = useState(false);\n  const [isDragging, setIsDragging] = useState(false);\n  const fileInputRef = useRef<HTMLInputElement>(null);\n\n  if (!isOpen) return null;\n\n  const handleFileChange = (f: File) => {\n    const ext = f.name.split('.').pop()?.toLowerCase();\n    if (!['xlsx', 'xls', 'csv'].includes(ext || '')) {\n      toast.error('Chỉ chấp nhận file .xlsx, .xls, .csv');\n      return;\n    }\n    setFile(f);\n  };\n\n  const handleDrop = (e: React.DragEvent) => {\n    e.preventDefault();\n    setIsDragging(false);\n    const f = e.dataTransfer.files[0];\n    if (f) handleFileChange(f);\n  };\n\n  const handleImport = async () => {\n    if (!file) {\n      toast.error('Vui lòng chọn file Excel');\n      return;\n    }\n    try {\n      setIsUploading(true);\n      const res = await importExamResults(batchId, file);\n      if (res.status === 'success') {\n        toast.success(`Import thành công! Đã cập nhật ${res.data?.imported || 0} kết quả.`);\n        setFile(null);\n        onSuccess();\n      } else {\n        toast.error(res.message || 'Import thất bại');\n      }\n    } catch (err: any) {\n      toast.error(err.message || 'Lỗi khi import file');\n    } finally {\n      setIsUploading(false);\n    }\n  };\n\n  return (\n    <div className=\"fixed inset-0 z-[100] flex items-center justify-center p-4 bg-gray-900/40 backdrop-blur-sm animate-in fade-in duration-200\">\n      <div className=\"bg-white rounded-[2rem] w-full max-w-lg shadow-2xl animate-in zoom-in-95 duration-200 overflow-hidden border border-gray-100\">\n        \n        <div className=\"px-8 py-6 border-b border-gray-100 flex items-center justify-between\">\n          <div>\n            <h2 className=\"text-xl font-black text-gray-900 tracking-tight\">Import kết quả thi</h2>\n            <p className=\"text-sm font-medium text-gray-400 mt-0.5\">Đợt: <span className=\"text-indigo-600\">{batchName}</span></p>\n          </div>\n          <button onClick={onClose} className=\"p-2 text-gray-400 hover:text-gray-900 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded-xl transition-all\">\n            <X className=\"w-5 h-5\" />\n          </button>\n        </div>\n\n        <div className=\"p-8 flex flex-col gap-5\">\n          <div\n            onDragOver={e => { e.preventDefault(); setIsDragging(true); }}\n            onDragLeave={() => setIsDragging(false)}\n            onDrop={handleDrop}\n            onClick={() => fileInputRef.current?.click()}\n            className={`border-2 border-dashed rounded-3xl p-8 flex flex-col items-center gap-3 cursor-pointer transition-all ${\n              isDragging ? 'border-indigo-400 bg-indigo-50' : 'border-gray-200 hover:border-indigo-300 hover:bg-gray-50'\n            }`}\n          >\n            <input ref={fileInputRef} type=\"file\" accept=\".xlsx,.xls,.csv\" className=\"hidden\" onChange={e => e.target.files?.[0] && handleFileChange(e.target.files[0])} />\n            {file ? (\n              <>\n                <CheckCircle2 className=\"w-10 h-10 text-emerald-500\" />\n                <div className=\"text-center\">\n                  <p className=\"font-extrabold text-gray-700\">{file.name}</p>\n                  <p className=\"text-xs text-gray-400 mt-1\">{(file.size / 1024).toFixed(1)} KB</p>\n                </div>\n              </>\n            ) : (\n              <>\n                <FileSpreadsheet className=\"w-10 h-10 text-gray-300\" />\n                <div className=\"text-center\">\n                  <p className=\"font-bold text-gray-500\">Kéo thả file Excel vào đây</p>\n                  <p className=\"text-xs text-gray-400 mt-1\">hoặc click để chọn file (.xlsx, .xls, .csv)</p>\n                </div>\n              </>\n            )}\n          </div>\n\n          <div className=\"p-4 bg-amber-50 border border-amber-100 rounded-2xl\">\n            <p className=\"text-xs font-bold text-amber-700 mb-2\">📋 Cột bắt buộc:</p>\n            <p className=\"text-[11px] text-amber-600 font-medium\">student_id, name, result</p>\n            <p className=\"text-[11px] text-amber-600 font-medium mt-1\">Cột tùy chọn: theory_result, simulation_result, parking_result, road_result, note</p>\n            <p className=\"text-[11px] text-amber-600 font-medium mt-1\">Giá trị: pass | fail | absent | no_result</p>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n\n        <div className=\"px-8 py-6 border-t border-gray-100 bg-gray-50/50 flex items-center justify-end gap-3\">\n          <button onClick={onClose} className=\"px-6 py-3 text-sm font-black text-gray-500 hover:text-gray-900 transition-colors uppercase tracking-widest text-[11px]\">\n            Hủy\n          </button>\n          <button\n            onClick={handleImport}\n            disabled={!file || isUploading}\n            className=\"flex items-center gap-2 px-8 py-3.5 bg-indigo-600 hover:bg-indigo-700 text-white rounded-2xl font-black shadow-xl shadow-indigo-600/20 transition-all hover:scale-105 active:scale-95 disabled:opacity-50 disabled:cursor-not-allowed uppercase tracking-widest text-[11px]\"\n          >\n            {isUploading ? <Loader2 className=\"w-4 h-4 animate-spin\" /> : <Upload className=\"w-4 h-4\" />}\n            Import\n          </button>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n```\n\n### 2.2 Update `src/services/examService.ts`\nRead the current file, then add these two functions at the end (before the last export if any):\n```ts\nexport const importExamResults = async (batchId: string, file: File) => {\n  const formData = new FormData();\n  formData.append('file', file);\n  formData.append('batchId', batchId);\n  const token = typeof window !== 'undefined' ? localStorage.getItem('accessToken') : '';\n  const response = await fetch(`${process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL}/api/v1/exam-batches/${batchId}/import-results`, {\n    method: 'POST',\n    headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${token}` },\n    body: formData,\n  });\n  return response.json();\n};\n\nexport const getBatchStats = async (batchId: string) => {\n  const token = typeof window !== 'undefined' ? localStorage.getItem('accessToken') : '';\n  const response = await fetch(`${process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL}/api/v1/exam-batches/${batchId}/stats`, {\n    headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${token}` },\n  });\n  return response.json();\n};\n```\n\n## PHASE 3 — Update `src/app/sat-hach/page.tsx`\n\n### 3.1 Add imports\nAdd to the imports from lucide-react:\n```ts\nimport { ..., Upload } from 'lucide-react';\n```\nAdd import for the modal:\n```ts\nimport ImportResultsModal from '@/src/components/sat-hach/ImportResultsModal';\n```\n\n### 3.2 Add state\nAdd to the state declarations:\n```ts\nconst [importModalOpen, setImportModalOpen] = useState(false);\nconst [targetBatchForImport, setTargetBatchForImport] = useState<{ id: string; name: string } | null>(null);\n```\n\n### 3.3 Add \"Import kết quả\" button in header\nFind the header buttons section (next to the \"Xuất Excel\" button), add:\n```tsx\n<button\n  onClick={() => {\n    // This button will be per-batch, so add it in the expanded panel instead\n  }}\n  className=\"hidden\" // hide this one - we'll add per-batch buttons in expanded panel instead\n/>\n```\n\nActually, put the Import button in the expanded panel per-batch instead of the header. Add it in the expanded panel action area (next to the \"Gắn HV\" button or as a separate action).\n\n### 3.4 In expanded panel, add Import button and absent count\nFind the section where the batch is rendered. In the expanded panel, add:\n- A new \"Import kết quả\" button\n- Update stats to include absent count\n\nCompute absent count:\n```ts\nconst absentCount = exam.studentResults?.filter((r: any) => r.result === 'absent').length || 0;\n```\n\nIn the stats box (where passedCount and failedCount are shown), add:\n```tsx\n<div className=\"flex flex-col border-l border-gray-100 pl-4\">\n  <span className=\"text-lg font-black text-gray-400 leading-none\">{absentCount}</span>\n  <span className=\"text-[9px] font-bold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-widest mt-1\">Vắng</span>\n</div>\n```\n\nAdd Import button in the expanded panel header (after the \"Gắn HV\" button):\n```tsx\n<button\n  onClick={() => {\n    setTargetBatchForImport({ id: exam._id, name: exam.name });\n    setImportModalOpen(true);\n  }}\n  className=\"flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 text-amber-600 hover:bg-amber-100 transition-colors rounded-lg font-bold text-xs\"\n>\n  <Upload className=\"w-3.5 h-3.5\" /> Import\n</button>\n```\n\n### 3.5 Update ResultModal for per-section results\n\nEdit `src/components/sat-hach/ResultModal.tsx`:\n\nChange the interface to include sub-results:\n```ts\nstudent: { \n  id: string; \n  name: string; \n  licenseClass: string; \n  currentResult?: string; \n  currentNote?: string;\n  theoryResult?: string;\n  simulationResult?: string;\n  parkingResult?: string;\n  roadResult?: string;\n} | null;\n```\n\nAdd state:\n```ts\nconst [theoryResult, setTheoryResult] = useState('no_result');\nconst [simulationResult, setSimulationResult] = useState('no_result');\nconst [parkingResult, setParkingResult] = useState('no_result');\nconst [roadResult, setRoadResult] = useState('no_result');\n```\n\nPre-populate in useEffect:\n```ts\nif (isOpen && student) {\n  setResult(student.currentResult || 'no_result');\n  setNote(student.currentNote || '');\n  setTheoryResult(student.theoryResult || 'no_result');\n  setSimulationResult(student.simulationResult || 'no_result');\n  setParkingResult(student.parkingResult || 'no_result');\n  setRoadResult(student.roadResult || 'no_result');\n  setTouched({});\n  setErrors({});\n}\n```\n\nChange onSave prop type:\n```ts\nonSave: (data: { result: string; theory_result?: string; simulation_result?: string; parking_result?: string; road_result?: string; note: string }) => Promise<void>;\n```\n\nUpdate handleSave function to pass object:\n```ts\nconst handleSave = async () => {\n  const errs = validate(result, note);\n  setErrors(errs);\n  setTouched({ result: true, note: true });\n  if (Object.keys(errs).length > 0) return;\n  try {\n    setIsSubmitting(true);\n    await onSave({ \n      result, \n      theory_result: theoryResult === 'no_result' ? undefined : theoryResult,\n      simulation_result: simulationResult === 'no_result' ? undefined : simulationResult,\n      parking_result: parkingResult === 'no_result' ? undefined : parkingResult,\n      road_result: roadResult === 'no_result' ? undefined : roadResult,\n      note \n    });\n    onClose();\n  } catch (err: any) {\n    if (err.response?.data?.errors) {\n      const serverErrs: any = {};\n      err.response.data.errors.forEach((e: any) => {\n        const path = e.path.split('.').pop();\n        serverErrs[path] = e.message;\n      });\n      setErrors(prev => ({ ...prev, ...serverErrs }));\n    }\n  } finally {\n    setIsSubmitting(false);\n  }\n};\n```\n\nAdd sub-section selects in the modal body (add right after the main result select):\n```tsx\n<div className=\"grid grid-cols-2 gap-3\">\n  <FieldWrapper label=\"LÝ THUYẾT\" field=\"theory\">\n    <select value={theoryResult} onChange={e => setTheoryResult(e.target.value)}\n      className=\"w-full px-4 py-3 bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-xl text-sm font-medium focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-indigo-500/10 cursor-pointer appearance-none\">\n      <option value=\"no_result\">Chưa có</option>\n      <option value=\"pass\">Đạt</option>\n      <option value=\"fail\">Trượt</option>\n      <option value=\"absent\">Vắng</option>\n    </select>\n  </FieldWrapper>\n  <FieldWrapper label=\"MÔ PHỎNG\" field=\"simulation\">\n    <select value={simulationResult} onChange={e => setSimulationResult(e.target.value)}\n      className=\"w-full px-4 py-3 bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-xl text-sm font-medium focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-indigo-500/10 cursor-pointer appearance-none\">\n      <option value=\"no_result\">Chưa có</option>\n      <option value=\"pass\">Đạt</option>\n      <option value=\"fail\">Trượt</option>\n      <option value=\"absent\">Vắng</option>\n    </select>\n  </FieldWrapper>\n  <FieldWrapper label=\"SA HÌNH\" field=\"parking\">\n    <select value={parkingResult} onChange={e => setParkingResult(e.target.value)}\n      className=\"w-full px-4 py-3 bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-xl text-sm font-medium focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-indigo-500/10 cursor-pointer appearance-none\">\n      <option value=\"no_result\">Chưa có</option>\n      <option value=\"pass\">Đạt</option>\n      <option value=\"fail\">Trượt</option>\n      <option value=\"absent\">Vắng</option>\n    </select>\n  </FieldWrapper>\n  <FieldWrapper label=\"ĐƯỜNG TRƯỜNG\" field=\"road\">\n    <select value={roadResult} onChange={e => setRoadResult(e.target.value)}\n      className=\"w-full px-4 py-3 bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-xl text-sm font-medium focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-indigo-500/10 cursor-pointer appearance-none\">\n      <option value=\"no_result\">Chưa có</option>\n      <option value=\"pass\">Đạt</option>\n      <option value=\"fail\">Trượt</option>\n      <option value=\"absent\">Vắng</option>\n    </select>\n  </FieldWrapper>\n</div>\n```\n\n### 3.6 Update handleSaveResult in sat-hach/page.tsx\nUpdate the function signature and body:\n```ts\nconst handleSaveResult = async (saveData: { \n  result: string; \n  theory_result?: string; \n  simulation_result?: string; \n  parking_result?: string; \n  road_result?: string; \n  note: string \n}) => {\n  const { result, theory_result, simulation_result, parking_result, road_result, note } = saveData;\n  if (!targetBatchForResults || !targetStudentForResults) return;\n  \n  try {\n    const res = await getBatchById(targetBatchForResults._id);\n    if (!res.success) throw new Error('Cập nhật thất bại');\n    \n    const batch = res.data;\n    const updatedResults = (batch.studentResults || []).map((s: any) => {\n      if (s.student_id === targetStudentForResults.id) {\n        return { ...s, result, theory_result, simulation_result, parking_result, road_result, note };\n      }\n      return s;\n    });\n\n    await updateExamBatch(batch._id || batch.id, { studentResults: updatedResults });\n    \n    toast.success(`Đã cập nhật kết quả cho ${targetStudentForResults.name}`);\n    fetchExams();\n  } catch (err: any) {\n    toast.error(err.message || 'Lỗi khi lưu kết quả');\n  }\n};\n```\n\nAlso update openResultModal to pass sub-results:\n```ts\nconst openResultModal = (batch: any, studentRes: any) => {\n  setTargetBatchForResults(batch);\n  setTargetStudentForResults({\n    id: studentRes.student_id,\n    name: studentRes.name,\n    licenseClass: batch.vehicleType === 'Xe máy' ? 'A1/A2' : 'Ô tô',\n    currentResult: studentRes.result,\n    currentNote: studentRes.note,\n    theoryResult: studentRes.theory_result,\n    simulationResult: studentRes.simulation_result,\n    parkingResult: studentRes.parking_result,\n    roadResult: studentRes.road_result,\n  });\n  setResultModalOpen(true);\n};\n```\n\n### 3.7 Add ImportResultsModal to page JSX\nAdd this at the very end of the component JSX (before the closing `</div>`):\n```tsx\n<ImportResultsModal\n  isOpen={importModalOpen}\n  onClose={() => { setImportModalOpen(false); setTargetBatchForImport(null); }}\n  batchId={targetBatchForImport?.id || ''}\n  batchName={targetBatchForImport?.name || ''}\n  onSuccess={() => {\n    setImportModalOpen(false);\n    setTargetBatchForImport(null);\n    fetchExams();\n  }}\n/>\n```\n\n## BUILD & COMMIT\n\n```bash\ncd /root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-fe && yarn build 2>&1 | tail -20\n```\n\nFix any TypeScript errors until it passes. Then commit:\n```bash\ngit add . && git commit -m \"feat(exam): enhance UI with absent count, per-section results modal, and Excel import\"\n```\n\n## RULES\n- Use yarn, never npm\n- Always yarn build before commit\n- NEVER push — only commit locally\n- Working dir: `/root/.openclaw/workspaces/teacher-driving-training-system.bootstrap-backup/ahv-qlhv-fe`\n- Report exactly what was done after commit\n","label":"ahv-qlhv-fe:senior-frontend","runtime":"subagent","agentId":"senior-frontend","mode":"run"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":214,"output":6496,"cacheRead":42919,"cacheWrite":7071,"totalTokens":56700,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776505248997,"responseId":"063284a29e25ed414cd83b2159e4bc08"}}
